<SUMMARY>
SUMMARY: 

This proposed rule establishes an alternative procedure for filing proof of fee payment for appeals of Immigration
Judge decisions to the Board of Immigration Appeals (Board). It provides added flexibility in the appeal filing procedure
by permitting a respondent/applicant to certify that a fee was forwarded to the Immigration and Naturalization Service
(Service). It further allows thirty (30) days from the date of filing the appeal for the respondent/applicant to submit
a fee receipt. It also provides that failure to present proof of payment of fee will cause the appeal to be deemed improperly
