a terminal would not be subject to the standards) and what level of control would be appropriate. Consistent with the
requirements of section 183(f) calling for the consideration of costs and other non-air quality impacts, as well
as the general requirements under RACT to review economic feasibility, the EPA believes that section 183(f) gives
the EPA the flexibility to determine the level and scope of regulation that is most appropriate for terminal facilities,
given all of the factors indicated. 

Assuming 100 percent capture of emissions (which can be assumed when vapor tight vessels are loaded), the overall
level of control is determined by the efficiency of the control device to which emissions are ducted. Currently, recovery
